{
  "slug": "passwords-are-not-a-strategy",
  "title": "Passwords are not a strategy",
  "category": "security",
  "kicker": "Authentication",
  "hook": "A password field is only one piece of identity. Treating it as the whole plan is how accounts become support tickets.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-20",
  "tags": [
    "authentication",
    "accounts"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Users reuse secrets because humans are human",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Password rules that punish users often create predictable workarounds. The better strategy is layered: password managers, multifactor authentication, rate limits, breach checks, and recovery flows that are not easier to attack than login.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "auth · login defense",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "password ok",
